description:
&lt;p&gt;As a Home Support Worker, you will be required to work with people in their own home, providing a range of care and support that maximises independence. This may include assisting people with their personal care, helping them to prepare meals and snacks and helping to rebuild their confidence.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We aim to get people out of hospital as soon as they are medically fit and work with people to prevent further admissions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;20-hour posts available, which include a continental shift pattern that includes mornings and evenings and you should be able to travel across the borough and will therefore need to hold a full valid driving licence.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The starting salary for a 20 hour contact is £11,298. However, enhancements are paid in addition, if you work on Public Holidays, weekends and evenings. You will also receive generous annual leave entitlement, and have access to a range of employee benefits, which includes discounts on shopping and gym membership. There is also the opportunity to join the Local Government Pension Scheme.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;An enhanced DBS is required for this role.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hours&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;20 hour posts available&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Due to high volume of anticipated applicants, we will only contact those candidates that we invite forward for Assessment Interview.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
